00:58:36.240 --> 00:58:37.830
that one learns, so I was wondering

00:58:37.830 --> 00:58:41.590
is it to do with the
learning, the activity type,

00:58:41.590 --> 00:58:43.680
or what is it to actually
increase retention

00:58:43.680 --> 00:58:45.850
of things that you've already learned?

00:58:45.850 --> 00:58:47.440
- That's a very good question.

00:58:47.440 --> 00:58:49.240
From an evolutionary perspective,

00:58:49.240 --> 00:58:52.550
we think of what we learn, it actually,

00:58:52.550 --> 00:58:55.260
there's two different types
of things that we learn.

00:58:55.260 --> 00:58:59.710
And one is like evolutionarily primary,

00:58:59.710 --> 00:59:01.800
and that is things like learning

00:59:01.800 --> 00:59:03.960
to speak a language and so forth.

00:59:03.960 --> 00:59:07.084
Well, evolutionarily secondary learning

00:59:07.084 --> 00:59:09.530
are things like learning to read,

00:59:09.530 --> 00:59:14.530
learning how to write, and
learning how to do math.

00:59:15.950 --> 00:59:18.494
Those come with more difficulty.

00:59:18.494 --> 00:59:22.140
And that is why, a lot of times teachers,

00:59:22.140 --> 00:59:24.160
with great intent, will say,

00:59:24.160 --> 00:59:28.634
oh, learning should always be as fun,

00:59:28.634 --> 00:59:33.390
in high school as it was
when you were a little kid,

00:59:33.390 --> 00:59:34.820
a baby, and so forth.

00:59:34.820 --> 00:59:36.250
Well, that's when you were learning things

00:59:36.250 --> 00:59:38.600
that came naturally to human beings,

00:59:38.600 --> 00:59:41.750
like speaking a language,
your native language.

00:59:41.750 --> 00:59:46.599
And so, I think that when
you're learning something,

00:59:46.599 --> 00:59:50.105
it depends a lot on whether it's a primary

00:59:50.105 --> 00:59:52.629
or a secondary type of learning thing.

00:59:52.629 --> 00:59:57.355
And it also depends, there's a,

00:59:57.355 --> 00:59:59.870
it's a really complicated subject.

